article.description: — Tyree Ihenacho had 24 points in North Dakota's 95-66 victory against South Dakota on Saturday.
article.headline: Ihenacho scores 24, North Dakota knocks off South Dakota 95-66
article.linkText: Ihenacho scores 24, North Dakota knocks off South Dakota 95-66
article.story: GRAND FORKS, N.D. -- — Tyree Ihenacho had 24 points in North Dakota's 95-66 victory against South Dakota on Saturday. Ihenacho also contributed eight assists for the Fightin' Hawks (18-13, 10-6 Summit League). Treysen Eaglestaff scored 19 points, shooting 7 for 14, including 3 for 8 from beyond the arc. Tsotne Tsartsidze shot 6 for 10, including 2 for 5 from beyond the arc to finish with 14 points, while adding seven rebounds. The Coyotes (12-19, 5-11) were led by Lahat Thioune, who posted 15 points. South Dakota also got 14 points from Kaleb Stewart. In addition, Bostyn Holt finished with 13 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
